15:32.998 --> 15:36.201
♪ Burning like a light ♪

15:36.201 --> 15:39.471
♪ Desperate in the night ♪

15:39.471 --> 15:41.707
♪ For something more ♪

15:49.315 --> 15:51.050
I'm telling you, Mrs. Pig,

15:51.050 --> 15:53.218
if you enter that
antique car of yours

15:53.218 --> 15:56.488
in Lady Baden-Baden's
antique car show,

15:56.488 --> 15:58.657
you're sure to be a winner!

15:58.657 --> 16:01.460
Now, let's not get
our hopes up too high.

16:01.460 --> 16:03.896
We've got an awful
lot of work to do,

16:03.896 --> 16:05.965
and very little time to do it.

16:05.965 --> 16:07.733
Mrs. Pig: I can't believe it!

16:07.733 --> 16:10.169
I've had that old car for years!

16:10.169 --> 16:13.138
Huh?!
Holy mackerel!

16:13.138 --> 16:15.341
Somebody's been busy.

16:15.341 --> 16:18.310
Mrs. Pig: And I
think I know who.

16:18.310 --> 16:20.412
Oh, those boys of mine!

16:20.412 --> 16:22.548
They're full of surprises.

16:22.548 --> 16:25.417
(laughs) I can't
argue with you there.

16:25.417 --> 16:28.220
Mrs. Pig: Well Bert,
pull down the rumble seat

16:28.220 --> 16:30.389
and let's take her for a spin!

16:31.090 --> 16:32.992
This is fantastic!

16:32.992 --> 16:35.260
I own a Clarence Cyclone

16:35.260 --> 16:37.429
and a Harvey Hurricane.

16:37.429 --> 16:39.999
There's no stopping me now!

16:42.234 --> 16:43.635
Mrs. Pig: Hi boys!

16:43.635 --> 16:45.838
You did a terrific job!

16:45.838 --> 16:48.407
Who in the name
of hubcaps was that??

16:48.407 --> 16:51.210
Pig 1: Uh, uhm.. Bert and
Schaeffer, wasn't it?

16:51.210 --> 16:54.079
I know that,
you pea-brained porkers!

16:54.079 --> 16:55.447
Who's the ring leader?

16:55.447 --> 16:59.184
Pig 2: Um, gee...
That would be.. um...

16:59.184 --> 17:02.054
Never mind!
I'll find out when I catch her!

17:02.054 --> 17:03.088
Come on!!

17:04.089 --> 17:07.059
Mrs. Pig your
car is beautiful!

17:07.059 --> 17:11.030
Why, that $100,000 prize money

17:11.030 --> 17:13.132
is as good as yours!

17:13.132 --> 17:16.402
Mrs. Pig: $100,000 !!

17:16.402 --> 17:20.105
Good heavens, you never said
the prize was that big!

17:20.105 --> 17:22.408
That's a fortune, Bert.

17:22.408 --> 17:24.476
and it certainly
would come in handy.

17:24.476 --> 17:25.744
Yeah.

17:25.744 --> 17:29.415
That kind of money would
buy a lot of peanut butter!

17:29.415 --> 17:30.816
In fact,

17:30.816 --> 17:34.153
it could buy a whole
peanut butter factory!

17:34.787 --> 17:36.488
Grand theft auto!!

17:36.488 --> 17:39.491
That's what it is!
Grand theft, auto!!

17:39.491 --> 17:42.995
Pig 1: Boss, maybe you're taking
this a bit too seriously.

17:42.995 --> 17:45.898
Maybe you should
just let them... go?

17:45.898 --> 17:47.466
I'll let them
go as soon as

17:47.466 --> 17:49.635
I'm holding them
over a steep cliff!

17:50.903 --> 17:54.273
I hope you pigs have
paid up my hospital insurance!

17:54.273 --> 17:56.108
We've got no brakes!

17:56.108 --> 17:57.743
Yahhhh!!!!

17:57.743 --> 17:59.478
Mrs. Pig: You know it's funny,

17:59.478 --> 18:02.648
the boys have told me
so much about him,

18:02.648 --> 18:05.451
but I've never had the
pleasure of meeting Mr. Sneer.

18:05.451 --> 18:07.319
Aarrrggghhh!!!
Huh?

18:08.821 --> 18:11.190
Well there he is, right now.

18:12.591 --> 18:14.827
He shouldn't be
driving that fast on this road.

18:15.527 --> 18:17.463
Why, he's out of control!

18:17.463 --> 18:19.465
It looks like he's
lost his brakes!!

18:19.465 --> 18:21.300
Mrs. Pig: And my
sons are with him!!!

18:21.300 --> 18:24.369
Hang on, boys!
We're going for a ride!!!

18:25.637 --> 18:27.806
Oooh! Oh, so help me!

18:27.806 --> 18:29.374
Pig 3: Mom!!!

18:29.374 --> 18:32.111
It's mom!
Mom?!

18:32.111 --> 18:35.447
Pig 3: It's a long story, boss.

18:35.447 --> 18:36.849
Give me
the short version.

18:36.849 --> 18:38.650
I don't think we've got long.

18:38.650 --> 18:40.953
Mrs. Pig: Jump boys! Jump!!

18:40.953 --> 18:43.789
Uaaah-ugh!

18:43.789 --> 18:44.890
Phew!

18:44.890 --> 18:47.059
C'mon Cyril!
It's your turn!

18:47.059 --> 18:48.827
Are you crazy?!

18:48.827 --> 18:50.462
And let this baby crash!

18:52.731 --> 18:55.234
Don't go away.
I'm coming!!

18:56.969 --> 18:58.303
Umph!

19:08.747 --> 19:10.349
My car!!

19:10.349 --> 19:14.019
My beautiful, perfect
automotive marvel!

19:14.019 --> 19:15.354
Wrecked!

19:15.354 --> 19:19.258
Mrs. Pig: Oh, Mr. Sneer,
I'm so sorry.

19:19.258 --> 19:20.526
Decimated,

19:20.526 --> 19:21.693
demolished,

19:21.693 --> 19:23.095
destroyed!

19:23.095 --> 19:26.198
But I still have my
Harvey Hurricane.

19:26.198 --> 19:29.168
I can still win the contest!

19:29.168 --> 19:32.337
Mrs. Pig: Excuse me,
but that's my car.

19:32.337 --> 19:33.405
Your car?

19:33.405 --> 19:35.274
Mrs. Pig: Yes, for years.

19:35.274 --> 19:38.343
Apparently there's been
a small misunderstanding.

19:38.343 --> 19:40.045
I'll say there has.

19:40.045 --> 19:42.848
Three small misunderstandings!

19:42.848 --> 19:44.216
Pigs!!!

19:44.216 --> 19:46.418
Y-y-yes, boss?

19:46.418 --> 19:47.586
Mrs. Pig: Boss?!

19:47.586 --> 19:49.521
That's right! Boss!

19:49.521 --> 19:53.592
Don't you think it's time we
were formally introduced?

19:53.592 --> 19:56.595
Pig 2: Oh, sh-sh-sure, boss...

19:56.595 --> 20:00.299
Um... m-m-mom,
t-t-this is our boss.

20:00.299 --> 20:02.734
Pig 3: Uh.. boss,

20:02.734 --> 20:05.270
t-t-this is our mom.

20:05.270 --> 20:08.207
Pig 1: And our name is mud.

20:08.207 --> 20:11.243
Mrs. Pig: Mr. Sneer,
it looks like you and I

20:11.243 --> 20:13.779
have a few things to
straighten out here.

20:13.779 --> 20:15.948
We certainly do, Mrs. Pig.

20:15.948 --> 20:17.883
We certainly do.

20:17.883 --> 20:20.786
Pig 2: Oh my.

20:23.488 --> 20:29.761
Lady Baden-Baden: And the
first prize of $100,000

20:29.761 --> 20:33.498
goes to

20:33.498 --> 20:36.235
the joint winners!

20:36.235 --> 20:40.639
Mrs. Pig and Cyril Sneer!

20:42.274 --> 20:44.443
You know, Suey-Ellen,

20:44.443 --> 20:47.412
this is a very sporting of you.

20:47.412 --> 20:49.181
Mrs. Pig: Oh nonsense, Cyril.

20:49.181 --> 20:52.184
I had no chance of winning
without your help.

20:52.184 --> 20:55.787
After all, half the parts
in the car belong to you,

20:55.787 --> 20:59.625
and half the prize money is all
I need to rebuild my home.

20:59.625 --> 21:02.160
I'm just sorry you lost your car

21:02.160 --> 21:03.462
because of all this.

21:03.462 --> 21:06.064
Well, it's
not exactly lost.

21:06.064 --> 21:08.467
I do know, where it is.

21:08.467 --> 21:09.801
Roughly.

21:11.136 --> 21:12.871
Fortunately
for Mrs. Pig,

21:12.871 --> 21:15.774
her old car meant new
hope for the future.

21:15.774 --> 21:17.209
For Cyril Sneer,

21:17.209 --> 21:19.144
it meant finding a new friend.

21:19.144 --> 21:20.846
And for the pigs?

21:20.846 --> 21:23.181
Well, some things never change.

21:23.181 --> 21:26.285
Just as a mother's love for
her children never changes,

21:26.285 --> 21:28.553
no matter who they
pretend to be.

21:29.354 --> 21:32.524
Pig 3: Hey, I found a fender!

21:32.524 --> 21:36.561
Pig 1: Great. Only 3,425

21:36.561 --> 21:38.530
more pieces to go

21:38.530 --> 21:40.532
before the boss will talk to us.

21:41.733 --> 21:45.537
Pig 2: Oh well,
at least mom still loves us!

21:46.004 --> 21:47.506
Yeah!

